I believe you should just double-quote the `$projectDir/src/main/resources` path so that you `build.gradle` snipper looks like this:
```
sourceSets {
   main {
      resources { srcDirs = [&quot;$projectDir/src/main/resources&quot;]}
   }
}
```

#### A bit of background ####
Now, this path string is interpolated with the Gradle `projectDir` variable. String interpolation is when you can use variables in a string to have that string sort of dynamically built at runtime. For that, you have to reference a variable with the the `$` (dollar sign) in front of the variable name.

Also, the error message is quite clear about the issue. Without the quotes, the `$projectDir` becomes a &quot;property&quot; of &quot;main resources of type org.gradle.api.internal.file.DefaultSourceDirectorySet&quot;. And that variable is evidently missing from that `DefaultSourceDirectorySet`.

